          "date": "2025-10-15 16:33:18.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-16138 kernel: change rq_integrity_vec to respect the iterator",
        "message": "LU-16138 kernel: change rq_integrity_vec to respect the iterator\n\nAdd the upstream kernel fix cf546dd289e0f6d2594c25e2fb4e19ee67c6d988\nto fix the integrity metadata buffer corruption seen on some nvme\ndevices.\n\nThis kernel patch is optional, the bug exists from rhel9.1 to rhel9.5.\nThe fix was backported since rhel9.6.\n\nThis bug only affects us when:\n1. the nvme device has T10PI integrity support, and\n2. the nvme device reports a max_segments smaller than BIO_MAX_VECS\n(currently 256), which will make the bio split.\n\nChange-Id: I61483f0c53900f83c5ccd5b02039b68e55f67668\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Li Dongyang <dongyangli@ddn.com>\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/59695\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Yang Sheng <ys@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
